    </div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Keep your kitchen efficient and reduce food waste.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Use Clear Containers:</strong> Decant grains, beans, and pastas into clear, airtight containers. This keeps them fresh and lets you see exactly how much you have left.</li>
        <li><strong>First In, First Out (FIFO):</strong> Rotate older items to the front and put newly purchased items in the back.</li>
        <li><strong>Group by Category:</strong> Keep baking supplies together, canned goods together, and breakfast items in another zone to make finding things easier.</li>
        <li><strong>Label Everything:</strong> Label containers with the item name and expiration date using masking tape or chalk labels.</li>
      </ul>
